                </dcc:declaration>
            </dcc:statement>
            <dcc:statement>
                <dcc:declaration>
                    <dcc:content lang="en">Decision rule: acceptance when the Probability of False Acceptance (Check H) does not exceed the declared threshold, guard-banded against the declared MAE, for every calibration point. Verdict: NON-COMPLIANT.</dcc:content>
                </dcc:declaration>
            </dcc:statement>
            <dcc:statement>
                <dcc:declaration>
                    <dcc:content lang="en">Guard band: k_w = Φ⁻¹(1 − PFA_threshold) = 0.8416, MAE = ±0.3. Acceptance limits per point AL = -MAE + k_w·u_std, AU = MAE - k_w·u_std.</dcc:content>
                </dcc:declaration>
            </dcc:statement>
            <dcc:statement>
                <dcc:declaration>
                    <dcc:content lang="en">PFA (Probability of False Acceptance) per point: P1=89.4% P2=99.5% P3=97.7% P4=99.9% P5=100.0% P6=100.0% P7=99.8% P8=100.0% P9=96.4% P10=97.7% P11=90.9% P12=99.4% P13=86.7%. MAE=0.3, threshold=20.0%, mode=combined.</dcc:content>
